      Trigger: All product-core items complete, idle cycle threshold met (1 cycle).
      Per BACKLOG_SEED_RULES.lnd, seeded new product-core capability.

      Gap identified from SPEC v1.0.0:
      - String escape sequences defined in SPEC but not yet implemented
      - Required sequences: \\n, \\t, \", \\, \\r
      - Parser currently treats all characters literally in strings
      - This is a core language capability blocking complete string support

      Created item:
      - ID: LNG-CORE-62
      - Title: String escape sequences (\\n, \\t, \", \\, \\r)
      - Priority: P1
      - Bucket: language-core
      - Target: runtime/lexer.py, runtime/test_string_escapes.py

      Rationale: String escape sequences are fundamental for:
      - Multi-line string literals
      - Tab-delimited formatting
      - Quote characters within strings
      - Backslash literals
      - Cross-platform line endings

      Next stage: create (awaiting implementation)
